The nation was on tenterhooks on Monday after President Jacob Zuma abruptly “instructed” Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan to return from a scheduled international investor road show. The move by Zuma fuelled speculation of a Cabinet reshuffle and that the long-awaited showdown between him and the minister was imminent. It has long been speculated that Zuma was intent on appointing Brian Molefe as the next political head of the Treasury, a suspicion supported by the former Eskom boss’ hasty swearing-in as an ANC MP in February. Molefe resigned from power utility Eskom under a cloud last year after being fingered in a “state capture” interim report by former public protector Thuli Madonsela. If you are already a subscriber, please click on the following link below to go to the full article: Gordhan recall fuels talk of showdown If you would like to subscribe  to BusinessLIVE Premium to read the full story, please click here: Subscribe Premium content is not yet available on the app. Please use the desktop site to subscribe.